      "layout": "default",
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b211-100000000001",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "title",
          "html": "The BFS Algorithm",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 40,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 120
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b211-100000000002",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "body",
          "html": "<b>Input:</b> Graph $G = (V, E)$ and source vertex $s$<br><br><b>Procedure:</b><br>1. Initialize queue $Q \\leftarrow \\{s\\}$, mark $s$ as visited<br>2. While $Q$ is not empty:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;a. Dequeue vertex $v$ from $Q$<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;b. For each neighbor $u$ of $v$:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If $u$ not visited, enqueue $u$, mark visited<br>3. Return visited set and distances",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 200,
            "width": 1100,
            "height": 600
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b211-100000000003",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "annotation",
          "html": "The queue enforces<br>level-by-level exploration",
          "position": {
            "x": 1250,
            "y": 340,
            "width": 580,
            "height": 80
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b211-100000000004",
          "type": "arrow",
          "x1": 1250,
          "y1": 380,
          "x2": 1050,
          "y2": 420,
          "position": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": 0,
            "width": 0,
            "height": 0
          },
          "color": "#2563eb",
          "strokeWidth": 3,
          "headSize": 14
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b211-100000000005",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "footnote",
          "html": "BFS produces a shortest-path tree rooted at $s$ for unweighted graphs.",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 1000,
            "width": 1200,
            "height": 50
          }
        }
      ],
      "notes": "Walk through the BFS pseudocode. Emphasize that the queue data structure is what distinguishes BFS from DFS."
