      "layout": "default",
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b411-100000000001",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "title",
          "html": "BFS on Large Graphs",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 40,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 120
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b411-100000000002",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "body",
          "html": "<b>Challenges at scale:</b><br>• Memory: queue can grow to $O(V)$<br>• Locality: random access across adjacency structure<br>• Parallelism: level-synchronous approach<br><br><b>Direction-optimizing BFS</b> (Beamer et al., 2012):<br>• Top-down for sparse frontiers<br>• Bottom-up for dense frontiers<br>• Switchover at frontier $\\approx |V|/20$",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 200,
            "width": 1100,
            "height": 600
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b411-100000000003",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "annotation",
          "html": "Bottom-up avoids<br>scanning all edges<br>from the frontier",
          "position": {
            "x": 1250,
            "y": 500,
            "width": 580,
            "height": 100
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b411-100000000004",
          "type": "arrow",
          "x1": 1250,
          "y1": 540,
          "x2": 1050,
