          "preset": "title",
          "html": "Summary and Open Questions",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 40,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 120
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-b511-100000000002",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "body",
          "html": "<b>What we covered:</b><br>• BFS computes shortest paths in unweighted graphs in $O(V+E)$ time<br>• The queue data structure is the key distinction from DFS<br>• Direction-optimizing BFS is essential for large-scale graphs<br><br><b>Open questions:</b><br>• Optimal parallel BFS on heterogeneous architectures?<br>• Approximate BFS for streaming graph models?<br>• Better cache-oblivious graph layouts?",
          "position": {
            "x": 80,
            "y": 200,
